name: CoreAPI Security_AuditLog
about:
Description

The CoreAPI Security_AuditLog API enables to access the audit logs that can be viewed also in the Audit Log tool.

With this API, you can list all audit logs within the system, view the content of each log and also compare the original and modified state of the changed artifact.

Prerequisites: In order for the API to work, you will have to change the endpoint in the General tab.

Operations  performed

Important note: Please review the definitions and the request/response bodies for each operation. Knowing how the tools works, will make it easier for you to understand the methods and the payloads.

In certain definitions, you will a description next each field. If not, view the example data in the selected operation.

/List

List all audit logs by providing a query. Within each object in the returned array, the UUID of each item is placed. This is the same value that /Get operation requires.

Request
Query
Response
